{"lemma":"طَرِيدَةٍ","slug":"طَرِيدَةٍ","root":"ط.ر.د","root_slug":"ط-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ر-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26559"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"driven away, banished, expelled, repelled"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outcast, fugitive, escapee"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tˤa.riːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26559","headword_ar":"طَرِيدَةٌ","root":"Trd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariydN","text_ar":"طَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", rendered so by the the affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wild animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, that is coursed, hunted, snared, entrapped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caught:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^idu","text_ar":"طَرَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female that is the object of the chase"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a male [wild] ass. (M * and K * and MF, all in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alb","text_ar":"الب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A number of camels driven away together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels that are stolen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of camels attacked by a troop of horsemen and driven away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.)       -A2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cane wherein is a notch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huz~ap","text_ar":"حُزَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put upon spindles and arrows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and upon a stick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thus used for planing them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safanN","text_ar":"سَفَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, A, L,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cane which is hollowed, and has some notches cut in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through which an arrow is put"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, A, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and repeatedly drawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to smooth it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AHeyth, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small piece of wood, in the form of a water-spout, as though it were the half of a cane, of the size required by the bow or arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are to be smoothed therewith"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AHn, L.)       -A3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oblong piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) of a garment (A) or of silk: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long strip"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, IAar, TA) of rag (AA, TA) or of silk. (IAar, TA.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of rag, which is moistened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wetted, and with which the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of oven called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tan~uwr","text_ar":"تَنُّور"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is wiped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miToradapN","text_ar":"مِطْرَدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrow strip"},{"kind":"text","text":"of herbage (A, * K, TA) and of land. (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuT~ap","text_ar":"خُطَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the rump-bone and withers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariydN","text_ar":"طَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence.       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariydapu","text_ar":"الطَّرِيدَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain game"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the boys of the Arabs of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called by the vulgar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almas~apu","text_ar":"المَسَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAs~apu","text_ar":"المَاسَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~aboTapu","text_ar":"الضَّبْطَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the hand of the player falls upon the body or head or shoulder of another, it is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almas~apu","text_ar":"المَسَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when it falls upon the leg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foot, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asonu","text_ar":"الاَسْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) but this [app. meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asonu","text_ar":"الاَسْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is not of established authority:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was also played by girls."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A6-  See also what here follows."}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","TA","AHeyth","A","AA","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}